text: Quake by the Lake was a two-part professional wrestling show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It was held on August 10, 2022 at the Target Center in Minneapolis, Minnesota. The event aired as special episodes of Dynamite and Rampage respectively. It was called Quake by the Lake because it took place in Minnesota which is known by the nickname Land of 10,000 Lakes. The main event of Dynamite saw Jon Moxley defeat Chris Jericho to keep his interim AEW World Championship. Moxley made Jericho tap out with the rear-naked choke to get the submission victory. The main event of Rampage saw Orange Cassidy defeat Ari Daivari.
